# Generative AI Minecraft Houses
---

## Problem
For this project I wanted to try to generate 3D structures, and I thought a domain for
this would be Minecraft. One of the most popular games of all time. Minecraft is a sandbox
that allows for infinite 3-dimensional creation, and notably for my purposes a well-developed
pipeline for importing and exporting structures, with a community full of people who have
posted their creations online.

The goal is to use generative AI to take some dataset of Minecraft creations, and generate
new creations that look reasonably good. Like something a person might have built.

An important constraint is the project must use Diffusion Models to generate these structures,
more on that later.

---

## Data

After scraping the internet for usable data, I was left with a dataset of 13,000 usable structures.
These are stored as 32x32x32 dense tensors full of ids representing the blocks inside them. Notably
the data has something like 8,000 unique block ids, but this is way to complex for this purpose.
Especially when many of those categories are exceedingly rare. We instead truncate that to 256 unique
block ids. Which encodes 98.4% of voxels. Anything not on this list is marked as unknown.

