## Architecture

The final model used 2 U-Nets (a type of convolutional neural net) with 96 Hidden Dimensions each,
as encoders and decoders from latent space.

After encoding the latent vectors are noised until they are complete noise, then denoised using a third
U-Net with 150 Hidden Dimensions.

The final outputs are pretty good. They show clear understanding of 3D structure, an understanding of structural
motifs, and a good idea of when to use what block in the outputs. These strucures are learned by CNNs, and show
why CNNs are powerful. They are powerful models for learning geometric structure in data, and are chosen for just this.

