## Summary

With a goal of generating stuctures in Minecraft, I built a somewhat complex generative AI model.
- It starts with a dense tensor of Minecraft blocks
- Using this data, it trains both an encoder and decoder to a lower dimensional space. A probablistic space.
- Within this space, a Diffusion Model is trained to noise and denoise latent vectors.
- Samples are obtained by sampling random points in latent space, running diffusion to denoise, and decode
latent vectors back into house-like objects

This project is an example of using latent diffusion in 3 dimensional data with some success. A strong proof of concept,
and hopefully a meaningful demonstration of the potency of like models.



